.:: Puzzle 6x3-Level-7-19::.
City: paris, colone, san-francisco
3 different pets are kept: chinchilla, mouse, frog
There are 3 different nationalities: mexican, russian, canadian
3 different games are played: scrabble, chess, billiard
The people grow 3 different varities of flowers: orchid, aconite, balloon-flower
The people use 3 different means of transport: bike, motorbike, roller
 1. the owner of the frog is somewhere to the right of the russian##5
 2. the person traveling to colone is somewhere to the left of the russian##5
 3. the owner of the chinchilla is on the left or right of the person traveling to paris##3
 4. the person driving the bike is the person traveling to san-francisco##1
 5. the person driving the bike is on the far left or far right##3
 6. the person driving the motorbike is in the middle##1
 7. the mexican is on the left or right of the person driving the motorbike##3
 8. the owner of the mouse is on the right of the owner of the chinchilla##1
 9. the person driving the roller is in an odd position##4
10. the person who growsballoon-flower is the owner of the frog##1
11. the russian is somewhere to the right of the mexican##5
12. the person who growsorchid is somewhere between the person who growsaconite and the person playing billiard##7
13. the person playing chess is in an even position##4

.:: Answer ::.
|               |      1      |      2      |    3    |
| City      | colone | paris         | san-francisco  |
| Pet         | chinchilla  | mouse | frog  |
| Nationality   | mexican      | russian       | canadian |
| Game   | scrabble      | chess        | billiard  |
| Flower         | aconite    | orchid  | balloon-flower    |
| Transport     | roller      | motorbike   | bike    |

